      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's heartbreaking when the tables are turned and you're no longer able to give, but that's exactly what's happening with your family. Recognize that it doesn't mean they don't care, but it does mean they're shouldering the burden of caring for you. Remember, their priorities are changing as they navigate their own lives, but the guilt is still there. Acknowledge their feelings, but also remind yourself that you're not a burden, but a priority that's still worth focusing on.",
